This paper focuses on evaluating the performance of Mobile Broadband (MBB) networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the measurement of mobile speed, which can be considered a security concern (cs.CR) as it can be used to identify vulnerabilities in the network. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of open source tools and the release of open data, which aligns with the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the complex mobile ecosystem, which can be considered a system and control (cs.SI) problem.
